This happened after I spent 12hrs on set filming the video for “SUV” . I’ll never except or be cool with encounters like this. People have to be held accountable. Period ! They gave us a number to file a complaint, we left several messages & still no returns. This post is to bring awareness. As African Americans or brown people we have to stay calm in a situations like this, use proper English to communicate how we feel despite being angry to deescalate. I’m learning how to practice this, it’s a harsh reality, but this is America.

Yesterday I was so sad because this phone has all my rapshit memories & accomplishments. I didn’t wanna do nothing . The @jaguars sent me tickets to the game & I almost didn’t go . I ended up going and I was still sad. Trying to get it off my mind . my videos with Oprah and Taraji, my brother’s graduation all of the sentimental moments, I could never replace again . Then I thought about it. God always answers my prayers, but he won’t answer them if I don’t leave it in his hands and I’m still sad about what I prayed for because when you pray for something you have to believe it in order for it to manifest. At that moment, I let go and let God . Last night in church I prayed at the altar not just for my phone for my family and friends and for the new year said amen . The driver finally responded this morning I I woke up this with this text . Last night in church I prayed and left it at the alter . The lesson I got was teaching me for patience, slow down and know that I have you when you ask me for something my child believe that I’m gonna make it happen because I always have, but in my time. I hope this word blesses someone today when you ask God for something believe it and stop worrying. Have a great day.
